Aaron Phillips / For Neal Portnoy/

['A contrary genius on the streets of New York

Today I met a man named Rasanova Davis who had been raised in a conservative Jewish household on the Williamsburg/Bushwick border, out in Brooklyn. 

He was crossing Fifth Avenue shouting the most incendiary chant. 

Of course, I had to talk to him. We blocked one lane of Fifth Avenue and had a lot of fun.']
